    "block_id": "page_008:block_077",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "This module aims to identify the vulnerability-inducing commit (VIC) by tracing commits based on the previously identified vulnerable code blocks. First, for each vulnerable code block detected in the prior stage, we locate its corresponding line numbers of vulnerable codes in the pre - fix version of the repository. Next, we leverage a combination of the git blame command and the analytical capabilities of the LLM to identify VICs. Algorithm 1 details the systematic approach employed for VIC tracing. Initialized with the fix commit, vulnerable line, CVE information, CWE information and method signature, it utilizes git",
